  <h2>How to choose: starter → advanced guidelines</h2>

  <p><strong>Starter (try a PNGTuber)</strong>: If you’re new, unpredictable about schedule, or on a tight budget, a PNGTuber gets you streaming fast. Commission a small pack (idle + talking + 2 expressions) and use simple tools to map sound to images.</p>

  <p><strong>Intermediate (move to Live2D)</strong>: Once you have regular content, upgrade to a Live2D model for smoother expressions and a more professional look. Work with an artist to get layered files so future upgrades are easier.</p>

  <p><strong>Advanced (3D & full VTuber production)</strong>: For performers, event hosts, and creators who plan to monetize heavily, invest in a 3D model with full-body tracking and motion capture. You’ll gain the most flexibility for animations, dances, and VR appearances — and you can always reuse artwork from earlier PNG or Live2D builds.</p>

